{
  "meta": {
    "source": "toy",
    "description": "Rounded-block-clip prototype fixture. 4 horizontal + 4 vertical residential streets form a 3×3 grid of 9 fully-bounded blocks. Irregularities: VW3 bends NE from (40,60) to (60,160) (top-right blocks become trapezoidal + bent-chain regression); HW3 jogs up from z=40 to z=60 between x=0 and x=20 (saw-tooth top edge on middle blocks); a dead-end stub branches N off HW3 at (25,60), tip at (25,90). L.1 loop-street fixtures: Type A (Benton-toy teardrop) — BENT-STEM branches off VW3 at (40,-80), BENT-BODY is a closed 12-pt circle centered at (85,-80) r=25. Type B (Waverly-toy couplet) — original HW4 split at the middle IXs (HW4-W + HW4-E) to make room for WV-S (south carriageway, z=125 bow) + WV-N (north carriageway, z=115 bow) + WV-CUT (bare cross-thru at x=5). Re-run cartograph/derive-toy.js after editing."
